info.headline: Coastal Flood Advisory issued December 25 at 2:36PM PST until December 25 at 4:00PM PST by NWS Seattle
info.description: ...COASTAL FLOOD ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 PM PST THIS AFTERNOON... * WHAT...Minor coastal flooding. * WHERE...Eastern Strait of Juan de Fuca, Western Strait of Juan De Fuca, North Coast and Central Coast zones. * WHEN...Until 4 PM PST this afternoon. * IMPACTS...Flooding of lots, parks, and roads with only isolated road closures expected. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...King tides Sunday will result in unusually high water levels at high tide. Minor tidal overflow and coastal erosion is possible.
info.instruction: If travel is required, allow extra time as some roads may be closed. Do not drive around barricades or through water of unknown depth. Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone property.
